'''''Stunt Copter''''' is a monochrome [[Macintosh]] [[action game]] written by Duane Blehm and published by his Kansas-based company, HomeTown Software, in 1986.<ref>{{cite magazine |date=July 1995|title=Macworld Online, Fun and Games |magazine=[[Macworld]]|publisher=IDG|issn=0741-8647|pages=43}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=The Secret History of Mac Gaming |last=Moss |first=Richard |publisher=[[Random House]] |date=March 22, 2018}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
The game involves piloting a small [[helicopter]] around a playfield. The player has to position the helicopter and drop a person suspended from the aircraft onto a hay bale or moving cart. If incorrectly timed, the person might fall onto the ground or injure the horse or the driver of the cart.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Prevost |first1=Ruffin |last2=Terrell |first2=Rob |date=1994 |title=The Mac Shareware 500: The Last Word on the Best Virus-Free Mac Shareware, Second Edition|publisher=Ventana Press |pages=117 |isbn=1-56604-076-0|chapter=Chapter 5: Fun & Games|quote=For some reason, the game holds a stupid fascination for a few minutes before becoming witless and annoying.}}</ref>

==Legacy==
After his death, his parents released his games and [[source code]] into the [[Public domain software|public domain]].<ref>[http://macintoshgarden.org/games/duane-blehms-source-code Duane Blehm's Source Code] on macintoshgarden.org "Source Code for Duane Blehm's games (Stunt Copter, ZeroGravity, Cairo Shootout), released into the public domain by his parents after his passing."</ref>

''[[MacLife|MacAddict]]'' magazine used ''Stunt Copter'' to demonstrate software compatibility of [[Mac OS X]] [[public beta]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Sammis |first1=Ian|last2=Reynolds |first2=David |date=December 2000|title= OS X Xposed, Software & Hardware Compatibility|magazine=MacAddict |publisher=Future Network USA |issn=1088-548X|issue=52|pages=40}}</ref> An OS X version was released by Antell Software.<ref name="toucharcade"/>

An [[iPhone]] version was released by nerdgames in 2009.<ref name="toucharcade">{{cite web |title=Simple Mac Classic 'Stunt Copter' Comes to iPhone |last=Patterson |first=Blake |date=March 29, 2009 |url=https://toucharcade.com/2009/03/29/simple-mac-classic-stunt-copter-comes-to-iphone/ |publisher=[[TouchArcade]] |access-date=June 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=StuntCopter |url=http://www.nerdgames.ca/stuntcopter.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170703045713/http://www.nerdgames.ca/stuntcopter.html |archive-date=July 3, 2017 |access-date=June 20, 2018}}</ref> In 2011, an [[iPad]] version of ''Stunt Copter'' was released by Apollo Software which is similar to the original.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.apollosoftware.ca/stuntcopter/ |title=Apollo Software - Statys |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120720222439/http://www.apollosoftware.ca/stuntcopter/ |archive-date=July 20, 2012 |access-date=June 20, 2018}}</ref>

In 2018, a collection of his games were uploaded to the [[Internet Archive]] and made playable in a web browser.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Duane Blehm Collection |url=https://archive.org/details/TheDuaneBlehmCollection |publisher=[[Internet Archive]] |date=December 27, 2018 |access-date=November 12, 2021}}</ref>

